{
  "texts": [
    "If the data are collected using a policy other than π i, then off-policy Q-evaluation would be required.",
    "Implementation via a series of A/B tests.",
    "In practice, π 0 consists of simply prompting a base LLM to generate relevant suggestions based on the conversation session and other contextual information.",
    "Trajectories from π 0 can be collected by deploying it through an A/B test, from which we can learn an approximation to Q π0 (see top part of Figure 1).",
    "After a policy improvement step (i.e., running PPO on Q π0; see bottom part of Figure 1) that results in a new policy π 1, we can deploy π 1 in an A/B test and track outcome metrics, such as the number of purchases."
  ]
}